args: Hee hee! I finally got my hands on some!\nOne whiff of this, and the prince is going\nto be aaall miiine...
Excuse me! I'd like to order some tea\nand pancakes, please.
There are so many people in here...\nWill I even find a seat?
Oh, Cibella! Come over here;\nI've got spare seats at my table!
What a coincidence to find you here.\nDid you stop by after some shopping?
Yep! I got an early start this morning,\nso I'm exhaaaausted. What about you?\nYou've sure got a lot of bags.
I have been shopping for a\ngreat many things as well.
Okay, come on—there has to be a seat\nSOMEWHERE. I'm STARVING over here!
Is that Melody?! Boy, it's one coincidence\nafter another today! ...Hey! Over here!
Hey, girls! Mind if I join you?
Not at all! ...Excuse me? Could we have\ntwo more cups of tea, please?
And I will have a slice of cheesecake.
Are you here on an errand for Cleo,\nMelody?
Yep—although I DID dip into my savings\nand buy a little reward for myself. Hee!
So we're all here to shop, then?\nHmm... That gives me an idea!
We don't have anything to do until our\norders come, so why don't we show\neach other what we bought?
All right, I'll go first. This is the current\ntalk of the town—Vinelle's perfume!
Ooo, I've heard of that stuff—\nit's supposed to drive boys wild!
It better at the price I paid for it!\nBut no cost is too steep if it means\nI land the prince's heart.
Sure, I don't see why not.
What? No, that can't be right. *sniff*\nBlaaargh! It smells like Ranzal's old socks!
*sniff* Urk! W-well, it certainly is a...\npowerful scent.
This is not going to drive a boy wild\nso much as drive him certifiably mad.
Which means my plan is a failure!
Now now, I don't think all is lost just yet.\nPerhaps you could use it to train yourself\nto fight in noxious-smelling caves.
Er...perhaps it would keep fiends\naway from the prince?
Ugh. Still, thanks for trying to cheer me up,\nbut I guess there's nothing for it.\nAnyway, you're next, Cibella!
I purchased a set of dumbbells that were\nused by a famous guild of warriors.
I'm still quite inexperienced as a warrior,\nso I must work to get better.
I really admire that you're trying so hard\nto make up for your shortcomings.\nI want to be more like that!
I bought some other things, as well.\nLet us see what we have...
Heavy bronze bracelets... Cursed boots\nthat weigh a thousand pounds...\nA solid-steel jump rope...
I don't think I have the stamina to\ncarry all of this back to the castle!\nWhatever should I do now?
I think you bought too much for even\nthe three of us to carry back!
I feared I may have overdone it.\nI shall be more careful in the future.
Aw, don't let it get you down.\nBut if it doooes...
You can cheer yourself up with the\nporcelain doggy I bought!
That's the reward you mentioned buying\nfor yourself, right? Must be pretty cute!
You bet! As soon as I saw him in the shop,\nI knew I HAD to have him.
Your shopping bag looks to be\nfull of porcelain fragments.
I bet you tripped and fell on your\nway over here, huh?
Oh, WHY am I such an oaf?!
Well, he's still too cute to throw away,\nso I guess I'll just put this head up\non my dresser when I get home.
What?! No! That's SUPER creepy!\nJust go buy another one.
I'll pray that he reaches doggy heaven.
Honestly, it sounds like all of our\nshopping trips ended up as disasters.
I don't want to go home empty handed,\nso I'm going to find a different perfume—\none that doesn't peel paint from the wall.
And after I return everything, I'm going to\npick up some nutritional herbs.
I'm going to buy another doggy\nand NOT break it!
Why don't the three of us go shopping\ntogether once we're done here?
That's a splendid idea; we can cover for\none another and avoid any more disasters.
Thank you for waiting. I've brought you\nthree cups of tea, some pancakes,\ncheesecake, and shortcake.
These pancakes are so big and fluffy!
This cheesecake melts in my mouth.
Hmm. Now I'm curious what your\ncakes taste like.
So why don't we all swap dishes?!
After tasting defeat, I think we deserve a\nbit of sweetness in our lives.
